    "updated_at": "2016-06-06T07:19:59Z",
    "body": "How is that solved? It's not really about the background color, it's about the fact that the content is missing (instead, we only see a white, empty space), until some fraction of a second later. Is there an event that shows the real loading completion of a page instead of did-finish-load? \n"
